RIYADH: Saudi Arabia’s King Salman Humanitarian Aid and Relief Center (KSrelief) has distributed 2,600 Ramadan food baskets at the camps of Rohingya refugees in Bangladesh, Saudi Press Agency (SPA) reported. Mondays’ donation from the humanitarian center will benefit 13,000 families, the report added. This comes within the efforts provided by the Kingdom, represented by the KSrelief, to support Rohingya refugees and improve their living conditions amid ongoing persecution in Myanmar. KSrelief has donated thousands of food packages, dates and iftar programs around the world since Ramadan began earlier this month.